<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[302,513,1640,1666]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tomé 
<emphasis box="[373,430,1640,1666]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
in the 
<emphasis box="[592,1144,1640,1666]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:31296775CE7DFFF286B7FC119A56FEDD:BC5F80B8CE7DFFF38470F9AB9B73F942" box="[592,1144,1640,1666]" name="Ivan de Medeiros Tinoco Microfossils Collection" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" stateProvince="Pernambuco">Ivan de Medeiros Tinoco Microfossils Collection</location>
</emphasis>
from Paleontology Laboratory of the Federal University of 
<collectingRegion box="[553,697,1676,1702]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
. The comparison was satisfactory, due to the posterodorsal angle being well marked, however, the species found in the collection is smooth with no surface ornamentation
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1460,2027]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,592,1748,1774]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Occurrence and associated fauna</emphasis>
. It was recorded in the Santo Antonio section, at the following depths (from base to top): 1.8; 2.1; 2.25; 3.1; 3.4; 3.85; 5.25 and 
<quantity box="[726,807,1784,1811]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" unit="m" value="5.35">5.35 m</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[818,959,1784,1810]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salitrensis">
<emphasis box="[818,959,1784,1810]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">P. salitrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is associated with all species of ostracods, except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poag" authorityYear="1962" box="[231,367,1821,1846]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cuneocytheridae" genus="Dicrorygma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[231,367,1821,1846]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Dicrorygma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christensen" authorityYear="1965" box="[383,521,1820,1846]" class="Ostracoda" genus="Orthorygma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[383,521,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Orthorygma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
?) 
<emphasis box="[551,660,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">dimorpha</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1460,2027]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,358,1856,1882]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Observations</emphasis>
. Among the forms belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1972" box="[849,1026,1857,1882]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[849,1026,1857,1882]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Pattersoncypris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in the interval corresponding to the Aptian-Albian, in the Romualdo Formation, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[735,1021,1892,1918]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis box="[735,1021,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Pattersoncypris angulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents a well-marked angle at the posterodorsal end, which helps its identification. This species can be smooth or with a tessellated ornamentation on the surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1460,2027]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="540" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,509,2000,2026]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Stratigraphic distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[524,595,2000,2026]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, Araripe Basin, Santana Formation, Romualdo Member (Silva Telles Jr. &amp; Viana, 1990; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poropat, S. F. &amp; Colin, J. P." box="[303,578,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="699 - 719" refId="ref16238" refString="Poropat, S. F. &amp; Colin, J. P. (2012 b) Reassessment of the Early Cretaceous non-marine ostracod genera Hourcqia Krommelbein, 1965 and Pattersoncypris Bate, 1972 with the description of a new genus, Kroemmelbeincypris. Journal of Paleontology, 86, 699 - 719. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 11 - 140 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2012">Poropat &amp; Colin, 2012b</bibRefCitation>
), range dated as Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Regali, M. S. P." box="[858,1000,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="163 - 171" refId="ref16461" refString="Regali, M. S. P. (1990) Biocronoestratigrafia e paleoambiente do Eocretaceo das bacias do Araripe (CE) e Rio do Peixe (PB), NE, Brasil. Simposio sobre a Bacia do Araripe e Bacias Interiores do Nordeste, 1, 163 - 171." type="journal article" year="1990">Regali 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Coimbra, J. C. &amp; Arai, M. &amp; Carreno, A. L." box="[1012,1244,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="687 - 698" refId="ref13416" refString="Coimbra, J. C., Arai, M. &amp; Carreno, A. L. (2002) Biostratigraphy of Lower Cretaceous microfossils from the Araripe Basin, northeastern Brazil. Geobios, 35, 687 - 698. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0016 - 6995 (02) 00082 - 7" type="journal article" year="2002">
Coimbra 
<emphasis box="[1118,1175,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
). Potiguar Basin, Alagamar Formation, Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Whatley, R. &amp; Queiroz Neto, J. V. Q. &amp; Coimbra, J. C." box="[490,741,187,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="790 - 799" refId="ref13890" refString="Do Carmo, D. A., Whatley, R., Queiroz Neto, J. V. Q. &amp; Coimbra, J. C. (2008) On the validity of two Lower Cretaceous non-marine ostracode genera: biostratigraphic and paleogeographic implications. Journal of Paleontology, 82, 790 - 799. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 07 - 008.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Do Carmo 
<emphasis box="[616,673,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). Cedro Basin, Crato Formation, range dated as Aptian (Tomé 2007; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F." box="[222,514,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="56 - 70" refId="ref17032" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. (2010) Ostracodes da Bacia de Cedro, Andar Alagoas, Estado de Pernambuco, NE, Brasil: Implicacoes paleoambientais e bioestratigraficas. Estudos Geologicos, 21, 56 - 70." type="journal article" year="2010">Tomé &amp; Lima Filho 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Jatobá Basin, Serra Negra, in strata correlated to the Crato Formation, upper Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[207,404,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tomé 
<emphasis box="[280,336,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). In the present study, found in the Araripe Basin, Romualdo Formation, upper Aptian.
</paragraph>
